The Nigerian Exchange Limited has announced the appointment of Ms Obehi Ikhaghe as the acting company secretary of the exchange until the appointment of a substantive company secretary. This was disclosed in a statement signed by the Group Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer, Nigerian Exchange Limited, Oscar Onyema. He noted that the appointment followed the recent resignation of the Group Company Secretary, Mrs Mojisola Adeola, from the employ of Nigerian Exchange Group Plc. Ikhaghe is a lawyer with over 13 years of experience spanning company secretarial, corporate law and general legal practice. She is a graduate of the University of Lagos and holds a masterâ€™s degree in law from the same institution. She has worked with the company secretariat team of the NNGX over the last five years.